inn1.comm: good length, slanted across the left-handed Cook, who lets it go a foot or so outside off
touch shorter, angling away from Cook off the surface, gets behind it and punches towards point
Cook gets forward, opens the face and steers a length ball through backward point to get off the mark
fullish, tight line on off, Bell waits on it and chops defensively into the ground from the crease
good pace, seaming back in from outside off, steps out and shoulders arms to allow the ball through
angling in, Bell gets across his stumps and works one behind square on the leg side
length ball wide of the off stump, doesn't get up that much and Bell lets it go
stays back and defends into the leg side
good delivery from Ishant, bit of bounce and it rises outside off, surprising Bell, who does well to keep it down from high on the bat, it skids wide of second slip and runs for the first boundary
length delivery outside off, left alone

pitched up and turned short on the leg side, Bell is home as the throw come in ... and it's a direct hit that flies away after hitting the stumps and runs for four overthrows out towards deep extra-cover! Quick outfield, then
over the wicket to Cook, still two slips in place, defended on the back foot
line and length outside off from Buvneshwar, Bell leaves it alone
pitched up and coming in towards middle and off, turned towards midwicket
bit of width and Bell pings this through backward point, that came right out of the middle, giving third man no chance to get round. Lovely timing
goes back and squirts the ball behind point again, it's fielded but they get one
on the stumps, back of a length and worked off the legs
short and angled across this time, Cook opens the face but can only pick out the fielder in the gully
back of a length outside the line of off, defended
gets across and behind the line to block in front of off stump
banged in and this doesn't get up as much as Bell expects, he drops his bat on it and pushes into the off side
oof, Bell gets an inside edge right on to his box - though that's what they're there for. The ball dropped safely on the off side
length and beginning to duck back in, blocked coming forward
tight line from Ishant, keeps Bell honest with another forward defensive - and that's a maiden
back of a length, Cook slashes and gets one down to third man

edged ... but it goes straight between keeper and slip! Lovely ball from Buvneshwar, the extra bounce again surprised Bell and this was a genuine edge, but it bisected Dhoni and Ashwin and rattled away for another boundary
touch short, in the corridor outside off, punched towards extra-cover
length ball, seaming back in from wide of the stumps, Bell lets it go
comes back in and raps Bell on the pad, another shout for Buvneshwar but the batsman was probably just outside the line
zinged through in the channel outside off, Bell watches it through
urgh, filthy delivery from Ishant, short and wide, so wide that Cook is bent in half reaching for it, but he swings his forearms hard and thrashes the ball in front of point
tries to cut again, this it too close to him, stays a bit low, and skids through to Dhoni
back of a length, leg-stump line and it hits Cook on the glove and rolls square
width again, Cook throws his hands and gets a thick chunk of bat on it, the ball flies in the air but it's well wide of slip and quick enough to beat third man
stays back and pushes a length ball square on the off side
another four, the best of the lot, as Ishant overpitches outside off and Cook leans out to drill a flowing cover drive to the fence
gets across to work a length ball towards midwicket with a turn of the wrists
full and in the channel, leans into a push to extra-cover

big lbw appeal, the ball jagging back in at Bell, who played all around it - but umpire Steve Davis shakes his head. Height might have been a question, it came back a long way but hit him in line ... looked pretty good to me
short and outside off, Bell tries to pull but doesn't connect properly and the ball dribbles towards mid-on
more pain for the bowler as Bell slaps a cover drive through the infield, again enjoying his extra life
pulls his length back a touch and Bell blocks
slanted across, again inviting Cook to scissor away a cut shot, but he rifles this one straight at point
tighter line to off stump, Cook gets across and defends
short and wide again, back cut from deep in the crease but again he picks out the man at point
round the wicket now, short of a good length and coming back in, Cook plays the ball on to his body
on the stumps, good length, turned towards midwicket
pitched up outside off, Cook tries to drive but doesn't get to the pitch, it bounces into the covers and is fielded - improbably, given the first few balls, that's another maiden
length ball, coming back in, Bell pushes back down the wicket
touch fuller, gets forward and taps back to mid-off
short ball, Bell goes across and whips this off his pads past midwicket for a couple
good length, slightly wide, pushed into the off side walking across
on the walk and crashed back past the bowler, Bell left the crease in pre-meditated fashion, turning the delivery into a half-volley that he drilled past mid-off
shot! Again Bell gets forward, leaning into an effortless, slightly arial cover drive that whistles through the infield and away for another boundary
angled in, tight line around off stump, played back down the pitch
fired down the leg side as Cook move across, can't get anything on it and called wide
Cook is beaten past his inside edge, he had a big old yahoo at a full ball and completely missed it, a few inches outside off
there's an appeal for caught behind, might have been a scratch of pad on it, but the umpire is already signalling wide as Dinda's shout dies in his throat
more damage for Dinda, who continues to bowl too straight, allowing Cook to chip the ball off his pads over midwicket
length delivery, angling in, closes the bat face and clips a single to midwicket
over the wicket now, short and rising on Bell outside the line of off, he shuffles across to block
tighter line, slightly back of a length and defended
round the wicket, tossed up on off, worked through the leg side from in front of the pad
full length, spinning a touch in, shows it the full face of the bat in defence
floated up on middle and off, Bell pushes one back past the bowler to long-on
floated across from round the wicket, drifting towards leg, flicked behind square
tossed up slower, Bell waits on it and chops one through backward point
tossed up on middle and off, leans forward and prods back to the bowler
tossed up wide of the stumps, driven back past the bowler
floated up on the stumps, worked through mid-on for a single
full and outside the line of off, again Bell ticks the strike over by punching through mid-off
fired through a bit quicker outside off, Cook goes for a hack across the line, bottom edges it through his legs and leg slip collects
tossed up on off stump, turned short on the leg side
pushed through wide of the stumps, chopped off the back foot straight to backward point - decent start from Jadeja
tossed up, pushed defensively towards midwicket
fired through a bit quicker and dabbed into the leg side
halts in his delivery, popping it out at the last second, carrom ball, I think, Bell defends
another wrong un, Bell picks it and punches a couple through the covers on the front foot
pushed through, played back to the bowler and Ashwin gets down to stop it
floated up on the leg stump, worked behind square leg for a single
oh, that's a beautiful shot from Bell, gives himself a little room and carves the ball over deep extra-cover, superb timing and that's the first six of the innings
flatter and faster, on off stump, blocked
pushed through on the line of off, defended again
blocked outside the line of off
bit of extra bounce and defended into the off side
slightly wider, fires the ball in, defended again - good comeback from Jadeja, after that first-ball six
pushed through outside off, gets across and clips through square leg
on the stumps, played back to Ashwin
on the stumps, turned through the leg side
again Ashwin pauses with his arm in the air, Cook waits for the ball and plays a pre-meditated lap, doesn't quite time it but he gets on to short fine leg
pushed through a bit quicker, on the stumps and worked to leg
tossed up, Cook taps defensively towards mid-on
fired through and Bell plays back towards mid-on
flatter ball, pushed down the ground to long-off
over the wicket to Cook, angled in and tickled with the turn to fine leg
lovely stuff from Bell again, reversing the hands and steering the ball past slip, that will run away and the boundary takes him to fifty
pushed through a bit quicker outside off, goes back and opens the face to get a couple behind point
tossedup and played back to the bowler
full but straying down leg - wide
floated up a bit slower, on off stump and Cook sweeps hard down on one knee, doesn't beat the fielder at deep backward square but they pick up another couple
tossed up outside off, played back toward mid-on
length ball, straightening on off stump, again Cook is sweeping and his gets hold of this one, creaming the ball through square leg, giving the man in the deep no chance
outside off, gets forward and pushes into the covers
touch short and wide, Cook throws his hands through a cut shot but picks out the man on the fence
pushed through, played back for a single to long-on
length ball, straightening outside the line of off, steered to third man
deftly done from Cook, reverse-sweeping a length ball past short third man for four more
goes back and pulls a flat ball through midwicket
tight line, drifting toward middle stump, Bell prods defensively to off
Bell almost gets in a tangle, playing late in front of his stumps, the ball bobbles towards short third man and there's no run
angled in, gets forward and pushes towards cover
and that lid keeps popping up, Cook leaning out to drive and the ball deceiving Rahane's dive at extra-cover, that will run away too, more good timing and a fast outfield
pitched up and let go outside off stump
width for Cook and he cashes in with one of his favoured shots, larruping a cut through backward point - he's enjoyed batting in India, hasn't he?
beaten, good comeback from Dinda, tighter line and a little bit of lift, Cook pushing and missing in the corridor
good length, gets across outside off, played back to the bowler
length ball, around off stump, Cook rolls his wrists and plays towards mid-on, where a diving stop prevents any further run leakage
length ball, outside off and played with the turn through square leg
angled in, straightening on off, defended watchfully

crikey, that's another sumptuous hit from Cook, gets his front foot out and chips over mid-off, it wasn't greatly overpitched but you can trust this pitch and Cook swung his arms cleanly through the line
full and flighted, Cook sweeps, gets a top edge and it loops out towards deep backward square, drops short though and that will be fifty for England's captain
tossed up nice and slow outside off, worked to leg
played back to mid-on
length ball in the channel outside off, punched to mid-off
this gets through, stays a bit low a foot or so outside off and Bell mistimes his attempted nurdle
wide, another gimme and Bell slashes through point, a good running stop on the boundary by Gambhir prevents four though
ferocious from Bell, he picks the slower ball, waits on it and then crumps aerially over extra-cover, Dinda just can't stop giving away boundaries
pitched up outside the line of off and pushed through the covers
goes round the wicket, angled in and played towards cover coming forward
tossed up outside off, clipped back past the bowler for another single
goes back and steers one behind point
length ball, spinning in and a bit of extra bounce, played from deep in the crease
tossed up and Bell steps across, closes the face and works through square leg
touch short, spinning away, Cook reaches out to tap a single through point
floated up on middle stump, Bell sweeps and gets a bit top edge but it drops safely into an untended part of the field behind square leg
full and outside the line of off, Bell drives into the off side but can't pierce the infield
back of a length, coming back in, defended on the back foot in front of the stumps
short ball, outside off, Bell backs away and baseball-bats one back past the bowler, mid-off misses it but mid-on gets round
another shortish ball, angled across, dabbed through the covers to the sweeper
almost a quarter of a half-chance for Dinda, as Bell mistimes his shot, comes off the splice and spoons a couple of feet over the bowler's head
cuts a short, wide ball to the man at backward point
tossed up, gets down, paddles a single to fine leg
stutter ball from Ashwin, Cook skips forward and punches his drive along the ground to the cover fielder
holy moly, that's a whack and a half from Cook, again leaving his crease as Ashwin pauses, he gets to the pitch and thumps a lofted drive back down the ground and all the way over long-off!
on the stumps, back in the shell and defended
shot! Another brutal piece of hitting from RoboCook, who has been programmed to ODI destruction mode - he rocks back and batters a pulls over midwicket - that almost went for six too!
pushed through outside off and defended into the covers
length ball outside off, Bell plays it on the up, driven towards mid-off, he runs his bat in as the direct hit uproots a stump
round the wicket, banged in, prodded toward mid-off from the crease
touch short of a length, angling in, played off the back foot towards extra-cover
full and straight, Cook steps across and whips it over midwicket for one - and Dinda had also overstepped
good delivery from Dinda, full bunger in the block hole and Bell's new bat can't do much with that, he drills one down the ground to long-on

full and clipped to fine leg for a couple, Dinda had overstepped again ... though it looked a slightly harsh call on the replay, he appeared to have landed a fraction behind the line before sliding over
full and wide, Cook swings and misses - could have actually been called wide, that, but Steve Davis takes pity
length ball outside off, played back down the track
flat on off, played to the leg side, Raina fields.
gets the single this time, punched past the bowler.
Cook defends solidly off the front foot. And Raina appeals for something.
ah, false shot from Cook. Looks to swing to leg and the top edge flies towards short third man.
flat, Cook stays back and punches to mid off.
good start from Raina, rushes off to his right to field as Cook tries to push down the ground.
short, Chris Harrisesque wobbler outside off, chopped away through point.
fired into Cook's pads from round the stumps, worked through square for one.
angled into Bell from wide of the crease, defended back to the bowler.
terrible ball, lovely stroke! Short and sliding down from Kohli, Bell walks across and laps it clean over short fine leg.
this was a full metre wide of off stump, but Bell reached out to play it to deep cover-point for one.
looks to slog a length ball on the stumps, it bounces away to deep square leg for one. Pretty average over, that.
stays back and guides it to the left of midwicket this time for one.
hurled in almost round arm at 96 kph, it kept low on Cook who came down just it time to stab it out of trouble.

This could be curtains for Bell. Cook tries to nurdle Raina round the corner, and plays it straight to Rahane who is prowling at short fine leg. They go for the single, Rahane lasers in a good throw and Bell is short by a foot. The third umpire sends him on his way.
and he's away with a back-foot punch towards long-on
Cook pushes off the front foot towards the off side but the ball goes to leg off the inside edge
the first ball is fired down leg side
KP steps out and taps the ball towards midwicket
KP stands well outside leg stump as the bowler delivers and defends on the front foot
driven off the front foot to midwicket
played through square leg for a single
Cook moves forward and towards the off side to work the ball through square
defended on the front foot towards point
played off the back foot to midwicket
Cook moves forward and pushes into the covers
superb, Cook picks his gap on the extra cover boundary and hits the ball into it by moving towards leg and lofting inside out over the infield
Raina responds with a quicker ball but it's down leg side
he's lucky to get away with this, it's short down leg side, Cook swivels and pulls but doesn't beat short fine leg
defended on the leg side
Cook goes back and plays on the leg side
KP steps out of his crease, the bowler aims for the pads, and the batsman defends on the leg side
KP tries to work the ball on the leg side but misses and is hit on the pad
a bit short and KP has enough time to wait and punch past the diving fielder at midwicket
swept towards deep backward square leg for a single
worked off the pads in front of square for a single
Cook gets down on one knee and sweeps the ball in the air, it reaches the fielder at deep square leg on the first bounce
another short ball wide down leg side, too far away for Cook to connect with the pull
caught at short fine leg! Cook moves forward to sweep but gets a top edge that lobs tamely to Rahane in the circle. A simple catch and India have dismissed both the openers
good length angling into the left-hander from round the wicket, Morgan defends to the bowler
pushed off the front foot to cover
too close to off stump to play the cut and Morgan is beaten, it was a bit on the fuller side as well
defended on the off side
played from the crease towards cover point
punched off the back foot towards long off
Morgan lunges forward and plays a reverse slap but doesn't beat short third man
nudged off the front foot on the leg side for a single, Morgan is away
KP goes back and cuts the ball from off stump to point
KP moves forward and blocks on the leg side
bowled quick on off and middle stump, KP is ready on the back foot and gives it a crack through covers, he cut that hard and the fielders chasing have no chance on this fast outfield
played off the back foot to the bowler
driven down the ground to long on for a single
KP steps out of his crease but isn't to the pitch of the ball, he pushes on the leg side
worked off the pads towards square leg
too short outside off stump, easy for Morgan, who moves back and cuts through cover point
Morgan pushes the ball off the front foo with soft hands into the covers and runs, Raina has to field the ball himself
defended on the front foot towards the leg side
Morgan tried to play that on the on side but ended up pushing it towards the off
driven to long on for a single
flicked through midwicket for a single
steps out of his crease and drives to long off for a single
defended from the crease on the leg side
good length on middle and off, Morgan was beginning to come forward but checked his movement and pushed the ball on the off side
he comes out of his crease again but Ishant cramps the batsman for room with his line and length, Morgan has to defend towards the bowler
a direct hit at the bowler's end could have dismissed Morgan! He pushed the ball towards cover and ran, Rahane moved to his left, collected on the bounce and threw. He missed the stumps though
the short ball and KP decides to sway out of the line and let the ball go
hit off the back foot towards cover, he doesn't pierce the infield
good length angling into off stump, KP moves across his stumps and defends. Only one run off the first Powerplay over.
Morgan goes back and nudges the ball towards midwicket for one
Ashwin pauses before delivering, KP waits before pushing off his pads through square
Morgan steps out and hits the ball uppishly towards the fielder at wide mid-on, Bhuvneshwar Kumar that was
swept firmly towards deep backward square leg
steps out of his crease and nudges into the leg side
shorter length and Morgan goes right back and pulls with power along the ground, there's a fielder in the deep
short of a length outside off stump, Morgan plays a flashy cut over the fielder in the circle at point, there's another man in the deep
that's cleared mid-on and raced to the boundary, Pietersen simply clubbed a length ball with power over Ashwin's head
a slower ball outside off stump, KP tries to swat through midwicket but is beaten by the change of pace
shot! KP drills the full ball dead straight, forcing the umpire to duck in a hurry, the fielders at long-on and long-off have no chance
short of a length at the body, Pietersen stays in his crease and drops the ball close on the off side for a single
the slower offcutter, Morgan wasn't in a position to play it and he ended up letting it go outside off stump
Pietersen waits as Ashwin pauses before delivering again and then he goes back and cuts the ball hard through cover point
now he steps out and drives the ball hard back towards the bowler
swept behind square and a fumble in the deep allows the second run

he's smashed it! Pietersen steps out of his crease, makes room by moving outside leg, and frees his arms, carting the ball towards the sightscreen. Ashwin's gimmick of stopping before delivering isn't working against KP
played to extra cover for a single
pushed towards cover from the crease
short of a length and Pietersen pulls from his crease towards deep midwicket
full ball with width outside off and Morgan flays it through cover with a flowing drive, beating Gambhir in the deep
that flashing cut, Morgan completes his bat-swing so quickly, slashing the ball to the backward point boundary. Once again too much width from Ishant
Ishant goes round the wicket and doesn't give Morgan as much room, he cuts to point off the back foot
that's a length delivery and it's disappeared over cow corner, Morgan simply swung the ball with the angle into him, lofting it off the middle
better length on a tight line, Morgan stays back and plays towards point
KP goes back and drives to long off
played back to the bowler
Morgan steps out of his crease to take the ball on the full and drives to long on
a full toss but he's got away with it, Pietersen hits it towards long-on
Morgan plays the reverse sweep towards third man, he hit that with a big bat lift
defended on the front foot
that's a huge six and I thought he had mis-hit it! Dinda bowled a length ball with lots of width, Morgan lunged for it, got under it and carted it over long-off
the slower ball on the fuller side, Morgan gets under it again and lofts straight, clearing Ishant at mid-off and collecting another boundary
cut off the back foot towards point
nearly in the blockhole but not quite, Pietersen gets his pads out of the way and drives to long on
the slower ball outside off, Morgan heaves towards midwicket but gets an inside edge that rolls towards Dhoni

Has Dinda taken the catch on his follow through? Morgan is waiting and the umpires ask for replays after conferring to check if the catch was clean. Morgan drove away from his body at a good length and slower ball and ended up hitting it back towards Dinda's left. The bowler grabbed at the ball with both hands and the ball lodged in his left. As he fell to the ground Dinda seemed to clutch the ball to his chest. That looks fine and Morgan will have to go.
defended on the leg side
played towards long on for a single
nudged off the pads towards square leg
defended from the crease to the bowler
played from the crease in front of square leg
Kieswetter stays in his crease and blocks
Pietersen's hit a full toss to the fielder in the circle at midwicket, he should have put that away
in the blockhole this time and Pietersen digs it out towards mid-off
India have missed a run out! Kieswetter cut the ball towards backward point and ran, Jadeja fielded and threw at the bowler's end. He missed with Kieswetter well short
driven off the front foot towards cover where there's a fumble

caught at long off, that is a huge wicket for India with plenty of overs remaining. Pietersen lofted a full ball off the front foot but didn't hit it far enough. Kohli ran in a little from the boundary and took the catch on the move while diving forward
good length pitching outside off and angling into the right-hander, defended on the off side
Ishant's back and he starts with a wide down leg side
Ishant strays down leg side once again
the slower ball on a straighter line, nudged on the leg side for a single
Patel moves back and across and flicks a fuller ball through square leg
good length and on off and middle, Kieswetter defends towards the bowler
nudged off the front foot in front of square for a single
stays in his crease and opens the face to steer the ball towards third man
good length on off stump, Kietswetter gets behind the line and defends
length ball, and Patel simply lofts it over mid-off, who is in the circle, that is a poor length to bowl during the slog
cut off the back foot to point
good length angling into the pads, played off the back foot through square leg
Kieswetter steps out of his crease, makes room to cut, but can't beat point
the slower ball on a good length, defended back to the bowler
Kieswetter tries to cut but misses, that was a skiddy ball outside off
that's rubbish length, Patel has plenty of time to pull the short ball to the backward square leg boundary
short and wide outside off stump, Patel slaps the ball through cover, giving sweeper a long chase to his right
lofted towards long-on for a single
The slower ball but the length was poor, Kieswetter made room, waited for it and then freed his arms and swung hard, lofting the ball over the cow corner boundary
that's in the blockhole and it beats Kieswetter
short of a length and quick, Kieswetter slogs at it but makes no contact
full ball around off stump, Patel stays in his crease, makes room and carves the ball in front of point
in the blockhole just outside off, dug out behind point by the batsman
driven to long on for a single
that's the widest wide I have seen outside off stump, it did not land on the pitch
in the blockhole outside off stump, squeezed out through point
good length outside off, Kieswetter hits it to cover
a full toss and Kieswetter can only chip it towards long off
shot! Makes room by moving outside leg and drills the full ball through extra cover, he hit that from leg stump inside out
in the blockhole, much better length, Kieswetter digs it out
too short this time, Patel pulls into the gap on the midwicket boundary, it was the slower offcutter but the length was poor
Patel backs away and has a thrash at a length ball, he was aiming long off but the ball flew off the outside edge to the third man boundary
in the blockhole again but Patel manages to play it towards long on
he's launched that over extra cover! Ishant pitches on a length and gives Kieswetter width. The batsman moves towards leg, gets under the ball and drives it far over the boundary
in the blockhole, dug out on the leg side for a single
full ball on middle, Kieswetter moves across and works the ball off his pads through midwicket
short and wide outside off, Patel makes room and slaps the ball over extra cover and into the gap on the boundary
too full this time and Patel hammers it straight past the bowler for another boundary
this is carnage, Patel making room by moving towards leg, getting under a length ball and launching in into the stands beyond extra cover
driven to long off for a single that takes England to 325 for 4, an immense score

inn2.comm: steams in and bends his back, back of a length and towards the body, tucked towards square leg
pitched up a bit more, in the channel outside off and Rahane lunges forward, shoulders arms
length delivery outside off, pushed towards point
too straight this, Rahane stays back and glances the ball neatly off his hips, using the pace to run it down to fine leg for the first runs, first boundary for India
gets forward to defend a length ball outside off
back of a length, blocked on the back foot in front of the wicket
that's the sort of start that would make Daniel Day-Lewis explode in anger, a sloppy, short ball down the leg side and Gambhir says "thank you very much" and flips it fine for four
short and leg side again, flicked through backward square to the sweeper
off-stump line to the right-handed Rahane, defended stepping across
touch short of a good length, angling back in at the batsman, blocked to leg
stays back and taps another short ball to leg
length ball, drifting towards leg stump, dabbed short and square with a turn of the wrists for a single
defended on the back foot
short, fierce lifter this, getting up more than Rahane expected, but he does well to swat it away, taking his bottom hand off the bat
short of a length, pushed across the left-hander from over the wicket, turned towards point
good pace from Finn, slanting the ball across, beats Gambhir's dabble outside off as he pushed away from his body
back of a length and in the channel, dropped short of cover
dug in, at the body, Gambhir loops it short into the leg side and midwicket can't get to it before it lands, they pinch one
bit of width, Gambhir cuts hard, not in control of the shot but it has enough on it to clear the leaping Morgan at gully
on the leg, stays back and turns to long leg
good length, nips back a touch and hits Rahane on the front pad as he propped forward, Dernbach was very interested but there was an insde edge first
short and easy for Rahane, who whips a pull shot through midwicket, nicely on top of the ball and it raced away
and a decent response from Dernbach, who whispers one past the outside edge as Rahane pushes uncertainly
pitched up in the channel, big stride and punched hard but Bell leaps to make an excellent stop at extra-cover
too full and straight from Finn, lovely timing from the batsman as Gambhir deflects it off the pads for a boundary to backward square leg
ah, he gets lucky this time, trying to dab to third man and under-edging it fine, a foot or two wide of the stumps and past Kieswetter
another four! Gambhir waits on this one, uses the pace and slides if off the face of the bat between slip and gully - Cook had just taken a man out of there
fullish delivery on the legs, glanced to long leg for just a single this time
good length, outside the line of off, gets forward and defends solidly towards cover
touch short and straying too far towards leg stump again from Finn, easy for Rahane to glide another four to fine leg
round the wicket, tapped short towards point
short and slightly wide, Rahane flashes hard and the ball squirts fine off the edge of the bat, beating third man to the punch
effort ball from Dernbach, tighter line and defended
dug in, still a little wide, cuts hard but straight to a fielder in the covers
fizzes this one through, good length and pace in the corridor, Rahane swishes and misses
goes back and across and pushes one to mid-on
length ball outside off, worked through midwicket, in front of the deep sweeper on the leg side
goes back and across to defend in front of off stump
tapped short of mid-on for another single
angled across on a good length, opens the face and steers one to third man

back of a length, on the pads, clipped behind square, using the pace, Samit Patel does well to slide and prevent four - but that's still the fifty opening stand up for India, their first in 11 innings
more easily won rewards, short and too leg side from Bresnan, the batsman shuffles across and helps it on its way to the rope
good length, tight line on the stumps, defended back down the track
gets across to block a length ball outside off
length delivery, maintaining that line on off, Gambhir shows it the face
wider this time and Gambhir is drawn into an ill-advised flirt in the channel, fails to connect
beaten again, this was too close to cut but Gambhir fiddled again as the ball flew through
bouncer, well directed but Gambhir rides it well, keeps it down and gets a run through backward point
back of a length, on the stumps, clipped through square leg
pitched up outside off, half forward and opening the face, turns towards point
length delivery, straight and worked unfussily through square leg
line and length on the stumps, closes the face and rotates the strike with another single to leg
shorter ball, steered to third man
on the stumps, stays back and nudges through square leg
line and length, on the stumps, gets forward and blocks
dug in, this rears off the pitch and positively hums on its way through as Gambhir swings wildly and misses
back of a length, opens the face and steers one to third man
pitched up, on the pads, glanced firmly through backward square but picks out the fielder
short and coming back in from outside off, stays back and drops one towards third man
another four, after a couple of quieter overs, again it's the batsman using the pace on the ball, hanging back and clipping to deep backward square leg with little more than a flick of the wrists
flat and reasonably quick to start off with, turned to leg from in front of the stumps
tossed up and pushed back past the bowler to long-on
sliding towards leg stump, pops up via bat and pad
pushed through, not much turn and sliding on towards off stump, plays late in defence

is this going to be close? England think they might have run out Gambhir, as he came racing back for a second after turning the ball to deep backward square leg ... but the third umpire referral shows he was just in as Kieswetter took the ball in front of the stumps and broke the wicket
floated up on the stumps, leans out to defend short on the on side
full and straight, pushed back past Root, who slides across but can't cut it off and ball runs to long-on
drifting in toward the stumps, closes the face and turned to leg
floated up on middle and leg, flicked through the midwicket area
tossed up tight on off stump, defended
opens the face, stays back and steers the ball to short third man
spots Gambhir about to advance and drags this down, basically making it a leg-side long hop but Gambhir misses as he swings across the line and they get a leg by to short fine leg
tossed up outside off, gets forward to drive through the covers
stays back and taps one to long-on
gives it some air, on the stumps, lovely footwork from Gambhir as he comes out and chips over deep midwicket, Bresnan almost gets there but slides into the rope as he makes the stop
tossed up, gets forward and plays back down the ground
on the stumps, pushed to long-on
short ball, goes back and again punches one to long-on
flat delivery, pushed down the ground to long-on
floated up, tries to play with the turn but misses, the ball rolls away behind square off the pad
short and a touch wide, slashed hard off the back foot and they get a second as the sweeper doesn't take it cleanly
drifting towards leg stump, can't get this one away
tossed up, gets forward and turns to midwicket
full and on leg stump, clipped calmly through square for another single
tossed up outside off, opens the face but steers it to short third man
beaten trying to sweep this time, Tredwell pushed it through a beat quicker as Rahane heaved across the line
tossed up outside the line of off, chopped towards point
on the stumps, played back past the bowler to long-on
stands up and punches another one down the ground to long-on
pushed across a little quicker, tapped into the covers where the ball is fielded
flat and on the stumps, turned to leg
nice shot from Rahane, goes inside out and lofts a drive over cover for couple into the deep
tossed up on middle and leg, worked to the man at square leg
full, stays in the crease and chops to short midwicket
get this one away, bit of extra pace on it, Rahane sweeps and it comes off the forearm before racing fine on the leg side
fired down outside off, blocked coming forwards
tossed up on the stumps, tucked into the leg side
flatter delivery, not much turn, Rahane turns the ball to mid-on
stays back and punches back down the track to Tredwel

and there's the breakthrough for England, as Rahane lofts high to long-off! Tredwell tossed up, inviting Rahane to get forward, he tried to go inside out again but wasn't to the pitch and got too much underneath the shot. The run rate had slowed a touch and that looked like frustration, which is odd on this pitch
round the wicket, floated up on the stumps, gets forward to defend
on the stumps, worked through the leg side
on the stumps, nudged towards the midwicket area
Root is bowling round the wicket to Gambhir, who goes back and plays to point
tossed up, angling in with the arm, punched to long-on - and that's fifty for Gautam Gambhir, well played, sir
tossed up and Kohli gets off the mark with a prod to long-on
flatter, on the stumps, goes back and punches one back down the ground - that's the 100, one over quicker than England
pushed through on the line of off, turned to the square leg fielder
round the wicket, tossed up and defended on the front foot
goes back and dabs a single in front of backward square leg
flighted in the channel, pushed through the covers to the sweeper

gone, another one to Tredwell! This dipped a little, just enough to mean Gambhir wasn't quite in control of the shot as he tried to flick through midwicket, it sailed in the air and Bell was in place to take a simple catch to his left
flighted outside off stump, punched into the covers
opens the face and steers on towards third man to get off the mark
on the stumps, pushed into the covers, can't beat the infield
floated up, blocked on the stumps
goes back and turns a single to square leg
pushed through on off stump, Kohli taps to leg
touch shorter, Kohli goes back and punches down the track, Root scrambles to his right and saves a single
full and outside off, gets forward and pushes to cover
watchfully defended back down the track
this time he loosens the shoulders, plops down the front leg and heaves a beastly slog over deep midwicket, only a few yards shy of being a six!
looped up, Tredwell still prepared to flight it, played down the ground for a single
flighted outside off, gets forward and finds a gap at cover
slides down the leg side, Yuvraj watches it past - it's a wide but Kieswetter attempts a cheeky stumping as Yuvraj shifted his feet anyway
stays in the crease and turns a single to leg
flatter trajectory, on the stumps, worked through midwicket off the back foot
length delivery, angling back in towards off stump, plays it late into the leg side
touch wider, full and doesn't get up much, Kohli crouches and deflects one to third man
good, brisk bumper from Bresnan, cranks the pace up a wee bit and has Yuvraj hopping in his crease, though he does well to draw his bat out of the way
good length, Yuvraj is half forward and pushes to mid-off
cuts his fingers over this, slower-ball bouncer I think, and Yuvraj is nearly trapped in front, just gets a sliver of bat on it and it deflects fine past Kieswetter for four
shortish, goes back and pulls one through square leg
round the wicket, pushes this across and too far down leg - wide
tossed up on the stumps, worked through square leg and they run hard for a couple
full and flighted, driven hard but well fielded by Eoin Morgan in the covers
lbw shout, as Yuvraj brings his bat down late next to his pad, but he had got outside the line
flat, angled in towards middle and leg, turned through square
tossed up on the stumps, Kohli clears his front leg out of the way and drills this down the ground, beats the dive at long-on
bit of width, goes back and cuts hard for a single behind point
short of a length and wide of the stumps, goes back and chops through point
banged in short again, at the body and Yuvraj pulls hard, this looks like it's got four written on it but another committed dive by Bell at midwicket cuts it off and keeps them to one
pitched up and pushed into the off side
good length, in the corridor outside off, steps out and picks a gap at cover
on the stumps, worked through midwicket for the sweeper
angled in on a length towards middle and leg, Kohli's bat chops down and pokes another single through midwicket
short of a good length and wide of the stumps, chopped straight to point on the back foot
width again, Kohli pistons his forearms through another vicious cut ... and again finds the fielder
takes the pace off, wide of the off stump, and Kohli does the same, opening the bat face and sliding the ball to third man
Dernbach may look like and east London fashion student but he grinds his teeth and spits a bouncer at Yuvraj's head, who swipes at it and narrowly avoids gloving through
short and straight again and Yuvi ducks this
length ball on the pads, whipped away through backward square for a couple
starts the over with a fullish delivery around off stump, defended down the pitch
that was rather too close to be cut, Kohli has looked to keen to play the shot, he has to be content with a steer to third man this time
arrives on the pads to the left-hander, and is worked to fine leg

Kohli's tried to drive this length delivery through covers, took a step out and went hard at it, the ball used to race to the deep cover rope when he was in that insane form of his, now a thick edge has gone straight to the keeper
and gets a pitched-up delivery first ball, on the pads, works it around the corner behind square

hello, how has that gone for six, Yuvraj tried to pull a short ball awkwadly, awkward because it did not bounce much, and a thick top edge, how can you call those fat sides edges anymore, zooms in the sky and lands beyond the deep square leg boundary
into the pads from round the stumps, cannot connect as he pushes forward
pushes a full one down to long on
tucked  behind square on the leg side
almost did him there, Raina down the pitch, plays for turn, there isnt any, thick inside edge saves him, there was an easy stumping on otherwise
goes deep in the crease and nudges it, but short fine will deny him the single
tried to work this fullish one on the leg side, seems to have got on to him quicker than he expected, bit of a leading edge along the ground to the off side
played quite well, again the short ball not getting up much, but Yuvraj is ready, front leg in the air as he swings it behind square leg
poor, hurled full into the pads, and Yuvraj goes into an extravagant flick, there's some connection, enough to send it flying fine down the leg side
turned to midwicket
Dernbach losing direction in his return over, straight and good length, way down the leg side
Yuvraj has got that swat-pull on one leg working smoothly, another short one, not too much lift on it, and Yuvraj sends it galloping to the deep square rope
no pulling this one, it is a proper bouncer now, rearing over Yuvraj's head as he crouches a tad
goes on the back foot and finds sweeper with a neat punch
gets onto the front foot to one floated in from round the stumps, and works it square to leg, Yuvraj has sprinted a run and almost a half before Raina's cry of NO has him applying emergency brakes
punched to long on
almost got him, almost, he seems pretty useful, Root, as a bowler that is, Yuvraj looking to work it to leg from middle, leading edge spoons up but cover is deep
and then he bowls it full down the leg side, fine leg is up, and Yuvraj does not need any more hints to lung onto a knee for a big sweep
and again, repeat of the previous ball, powerful sweep and short fine begins the task of turning around to fetch it from the rope
staying in the crease, the ball is pitched up, have we seen that before, defended
Dernbach has decided his line is going to be on the pads with two left-handers in the middle, strange, an easy tuck to fine leg
leading edges coming frequently now, yuvraj is eyeing midwicket every now and then, the ball pops up in the air, but quite short of mid off
a bit of a pick-up, slightly helicopter style, from around off stump, rolls away to mid on

this bouncer bounced a lot, and Yuvraj has swatted it tennis top spin style in front of square, Samit Patel has made quite a mess of it in the deep with his slide, and Yuvraj has a four to go along with his half-century
once again, Dernbach is around that leg stump, and once again Yuvraj ends up popping the ball in the air, far in front of midwicket though
goes back to try and make some room for a punch to the leg side, midwicket dives, takes pace off it
across and whipping it with the inward angle, but straight to short fine leg
big lunge, big sweep, but no big connection, ball dribbles to deep square
slower through the air, well bowled, Raina adjusts to push to off
stays back to a pitched up delivery and tries to push to off, cut off by extra cover
Raina yet to find some rhythm, nudges this straight to midwicket and Yuvraj applies the brakes midway up the pitch again
Root sends his first delivery of the over down the leg side, just like he did with the last two of his previous, missed sweep from Yuvraj, loud appeal from the keeper for caught behind
low full toss, Raina lays into it and slogs it past midwicket
slows it down, tosses it up, Raina leaves the crease, gets too close to the pitch, still manages to beat extra cover's dive with the drive
wristily eases a full one to long on
Root's not done badly, but this is one delivery down leg way too many, now Raina helps himself with a sweep past short fine
looked to slam it through extra cover inside out as he charged out, found the fielder, who is standing up
moves across and works it in front of square for one
Raina gets some width for the cut, not a full blooded one, but still in the gap, a dive at point takes the zip off the stroke
comes down the track and has to defend a tossed up one down the pitch
defence again, now off the back foot
another sweep down to fine leg
punched back to the bowler
pushed with the spin to leg
nudged square to leg for one
straightish delivery, punched straight to the bowler
another punch, straight past the non-striker, long on fields
full, worked away stylishly, but right to midwicket, appeal for run out, Yuvraj was miles in his crease
moves across before the ball has been bowled, can't do more than nudge it wide of short fine
fine line, just outside off stump, punched to extra cover
angled in, and right away he goes down on a knee for the sweep, in the air, wide of short fine, but square leg is now finer
well, if you stick to one line, be it down leg even, it can work in your favour ultimately, Yuvraj trying to paddle a quickish delivery fine, ends up spooning it for a dolly to short fine leg
flighted nicely full outside off, MS drives, finds mid off
takes front foot across and nudges it with the spin to leg

talk about the pace of the outfield and the timing on this stroke, Raina moved to leg a tad, and managed to squeeze this length ball past the army of men in the circle on the off, away to the deep extra cover rope, absolutely nothing more than a soft push
worked behind square and they race back for two
moving across now even as the  bowler reaches the crease, but the line is too tight, and he pushes it down the pitch
Raina skips out, the couple of paces give him momentum, and he uses it to slice a full delivery over cover
slower one, gone wrong, foot down the leg side, what is with England's love of that particular region today?
excellent comeback from Finn, back of a length, angled across, ending not far from off, Raina hops a bit and blocks
moves across the left-hander from a good length, guided down to third man
Dernbach, full, leg side, flick, four, sigh
short fine saves another boundary with a dive to his left, Raina moving across and tucking a length ball off middle and leg
around middle and off now, he goes across once more and tucks it square

Dhoni gives the cut a lot of effort, Morgan saves a certain boundary with a leap to his left, did that carry, would have been an incredible take, yes it did carry, pretty low, but it carried because Morgan was quick enough to get a hand there so soon
finds absolutely no timing on a forcing punch
Finn keeping Raina quiet with a shortish delivery banged in around off, Raina gets on his toes to keep it down
Raina backing away and trying his luck at the cut-dab, no connection
slightly short, he pulls with an extravagant swivel through square leg
pacy delivery hurrying into Dhoni from a good length, worked to leg and he is away
slow bouncer, Raina has to wait even as he gets across, and then paddles it behind square
no width, pushed to the off side, Finn coming back with a tight over
tries to force it through midwicket, but it wasn't short enough
just short, just short of captain Cook running to his right at mid off, Raina looking to loft it down the ground, Cook tried to get there as it remained in the air for some time, in vain
cut away to third man
nudged off the pads but no beating short fine this time
lovely connection for Raina now, pitched up, middle stump, Raina lifts that over wide mid on
you know the routine, Dernbach, full on leg stump yet again this evening, and Raina helping himself
Dhoni comes out, but Dernbach shortens the length, squeezed out to point
beaten as he tries to run it to third man
slow and short, not much lift on it, he adjusts to swing it square, Dhoni shouts No as Raina revs up for the second
tucked to midwicket, short of a good length, zipping into Dhoni
leg side, but Dhoni cannot beat short fine leg, straight to the man, Raina scampers across, throw misses

sharp catch at third man, Bresnan the man doing it tumbling forward, that went quickly to him, Raina slicing it in the air, but wait, they ask the third umpire, and the ball, while still in Bresnan's right hand seems to have touched the ground as he rolls over, big moment
hit hard down the pitch, bursts out of the bowler's hands
no room for the cut, but Dhoni slaps it to sweeper somehow
a flail at a quickish one outside off, but on the bounce to short third
that is in the gap over midwicket, just a clever lift, big slide in the deep prevents four
single down the ground to long on
well bowled, Dhoni looked set to jump out, Patel spears it in flat, it pops up off pad, keeper gets to it square on the leg side, appeal for a catch as well
moves across and punches through midwicket, Raina gets to fifty
Dhoni brings Khandheri alive with a couple of steps out and a bulldozer of a six over wide long on
flat delivery next, Dhoni whips it through square leg
four for Tredwell, excellent spell, Dhoni not pleased, ball kicks from a length at Raina, who has moved across looking for the punch to leg, he has ended up spooning it to the bowler
defended off the front foot
quick and sharp around off, pushed towards point
Dhoniiii down the track, and straight over the bowler, not to the pitch, but that does not matter with his brute power
stays back and it almost skids through, before he pushes it back
one-handed, Dhoni with another six, leaving the crease once again, again not to the pitch, but that bat-swing sends the ball to the edge of the 90-yard field, even as he takes a hand off the bat
flat delivery worked to leg
Jadeja dances out now, but he mishits the slog along the ground through square leg
back of a length, worked to deep square leg
Dhoni steps out, Bresnan goes wide outside off, too wide
the man shows off his power again, this is not a small boundary by any means, full delivery, around off stump, Dhoni cracks it way over long on
right on the marker, right on it, Dhoni letting it go in the hope of a wide call
full toss patted down to long off

Jadeja wants to pull, but the short ball has come up to him fast, off from near the gloves, they want two, the ball has barely made it outside the circle at square leg, direct hit, but not only is Dhoni powerful, he is also seriously quick
down to long on for one
oh dear me, Dernbach has started with a slower one a meter down the leg side
worked to the leg side for one
Dernbach, all those leg side gifts may be forgiven, for you have come up with a slower full delivery outside off, that Dhoni has scooped up straight to long off
short ball, rising up awkwardly for Jadeja, drops it towards midwicket for one
runs it to third man with an open face
Jadeja goes, Dernbach running away with the game now, short again, tries to pull it, bottom-edge disturbs the stumps
another bottom edge but that is from wide outside off and needs a dive from the keeper down leg to save four
wants to tuck it to leg, but cannot find the connection, hard to do that when you are hit on the glove, gets the single anyway, and seems to have taken quite a blow
slower and widish delivery, Bhuvneshwar beaten completely by it
short is the mode of operation at the moment, Bhuvneshwar awkwardly works it to leg
criticise him all you want but the man has some incredible timing with the bat, hanging his bat out to one outside off, and next instant, it beats third man, who wasn;t that far away
and now he walks away to leg to try and go towards third man again, almost plays on
walks out of the crease and lifts it over midwicket, just about, man in the deep fields
that will go, takes a step to leg and creams a length ball past extra cover
almost top-edged it to extra cover, just eludes the man running back to his right
dropped near the pitch to the off side for one
moves across, fetches it from outside off and finds midwicket
squeezes a wide yorker past point, third man cuts it off
full delivery, he drives, extra cover is deep and keeps them to one
not a bad drive at all, pings extra cover on the bounce, Bhuvneshwar had no chance had the throw hit, he'd given up
Ashwin gets the crowd going again, walks out, and lifts a length ball over wide mid on, no one in the deep there
that will be it, Finn exults, Ashwin backed away to leg, it was a slow offcutter of a bouncer, Ashwin's thin edge of a flail ends in the keeper's gloves
Dinda swings at a length ball, thick inside edge onto pad, and to the bowler
Dinda goes over the bowler, but the lack of timing on that will take it only as far as mid off
short and just outside off, dropped towards point for one
boundary first ball, Bhuvneshwar swings at a full one, thick-edge flies wide of the keeper
high full toss, high enough to be called no-ball, a surprised Bhuvneshwar pats it back
slammed straight to extra cover on the edge of the circle, does not take the single
single taken now, Bhuvneshwar's heave sends the full toss wide of midwicket as the bat turns in his hands
another full toss, Dinda carves it through point, sweeper cover runs across to keep them to two
Bresnan strikes, Dinda's middle stump is rattled, so is off, some inswing there on the yorker, Dinda's bat-swing in vain
another full toss, pushed through point, Ishant will keep strike, not sure how sensible that is
thick edge first ball once again, just past the wicketkeeper, Dernbach doing nothing wrong with a full one around off, Ishant having a go
now a full toss and Ishant cannot connect
raining thick edges in Saurashtra, keeper gets a glove out to save what would have been another boundary
single taken in the end, Bhuvneshwar backing away to leg, Dernbach almost sneaking through, Bhunveshwar somehow hits the non-striker's stumps
squeezes a near-yorker to sweeper cover, and Cook knows it is England's game certainly now, thick edges or not
can only defend this full one, from back of the hand, out to off as it kicks from a length, and England have won an ODI in India after going 0-5 and 0-5 last two times
